   <mods:abstract>Littlepage arrived and then left for Warsaw. Regrets it is possible for
            any one individual to malign a faithful public servant, and require him to defend
            himself against presumptions of guilt. A passage deleted, probably by a later hand,
            states Jefferson's feeling that such attacks are preferable to limiting the freedom of
            the press, and that they are part of the burden of public office
            holding.</mods:abstract>
